      "label": "6",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Do EACH of the following:"
        }
      ],
      "resources": [],
      "sub_requirements": [
        {
          "id": "10288",
          "label": "a",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Explain how railroad signals operate and show two basic signal types using color or configuration."
            }
          ],
          "resources": [],
          "sub_requirements": []
        },
        {
          "id": "10289",
          "label": "b",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Explain the meaning of three horn signals."
            }
          ],
          "resources": [],
          "sub_requirements": []
        },
        {
          "id": "10290",
          "label": "c",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Describe a way to signal a train for an emergency stop."
            }
          ],
          "resources": [],
          "sub_requirements": []
        },
        {
          "id": "10291",
          "label": "d",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Explain the use and function of the EOTD (end-of-train device), or FRED (flashing rear end device), used on the last car of most freight trains."
